summary: So i brought this Build-A-Bear online because he was no longer stocked at my local. He has a heart beat and smells of bubblegum....
body:
So i brought this Build-A-Bear online because he was no longer stocked at my local. He has a heart beat and smells of bubblegum.

For those of you who dont know, the sents you can add are hard discs, and since this bear is softer than i normaly have them stuffed, I was feeling around for the disc to see where they put it. And i found it… in his crotch….

Right where my finger is is where he smells like bubblegum.

So this is Spider-Bear aka Peter, whos crotch smells like bubblegum.

blog.description: A place for all my nerdy thoughts.

title: Spider-Man Annual #1
body:
So in and of itself, that was a fine story. Giving Miles so more motivation to do what he does. But looking at it in the context of Miles as a whole, I don’t like it. Yeah, he wasn’t close to that Brent guy, but he died right next to Miles while he was doing some superheroing. That would leave a HUGE mark on someone. This story would have come up at some point before now. This is a huge attention to Miles’ origin story. I am not a fan. The second story was cute, but inconsequential. 

-Chuck
